Here’s the fastest path to adding **voice input + voice output** to your Mastra app, plus a minimal working example you can copy‑paste.

---

## What you need to set up
To enable full voice interactions (users speak → agent thinks → agent replies in audio), you only need:

### 1. An agent  
Your normal Mastra agent—nothing special here.

### 2. A voice provider  
You choose one depending on needs:

- **OpenAI Voice (TTS + STT)**
- **Deepgram (TTS + STT)**
- **Google (TTS + STT)**
- **OpenAI Realtime (Speech‑to‑Speech)** if you want real-time conversations
- **CompositeVoice** if you want STT from one provider and TTS from another

### 3. Audio utilities (optional but usually needed)
For Node.js:
- `@mastra/node-audio` → microphone input + playback

### 4. Wiring it all together  
You either:
- **TTS + STT mode** → handle audio in/out manually  
- **Realtime STS mode** → open a realtime session and stream audio back and forth

---

## Basic working example (TTS + STT round‑trip)

### Install the needed packages
```
pnpm add @mastra/core @mastra/voice-openai @mastra/node-audio
```

### Minimal code
```ts
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { OpenAIVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai";
import { getMicrophoneStream, playAudio } from "@mastra/node-audio";

const agent = new Agent({
  id: "voice-agent",
  name: "Voice Agent",
  model: "openai/gpt-5.1",
  instructions: "You speak to the user verbally.",
  voice: new OpenAIVoice(), // defaults to Whisper STT + TTS model
});

async function run() {
  // 1. Listen to the user
  const mic = getMicrophoneStream();
  const transcript = await agent.voice.listen(mic);
  console.log("User said:", transcript);

  // 2. Generate a response
  const { text } = await agent.generate(transcript);

  // 3. Speak it back
  const audio = await agent.voice.speak(text);
  playAudio(audio);
}

run();
```

This gives you:
- microphone → STT  
- agent → text  
- TTS → voice reply played out loud  

---

## Real‑time voice‑to‑voice example (OpenAI Realtime)

If you want **continuous conversation** like ChatGPT voice mode:

```ts
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { OpenAIRealtimeVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai-realtime";
import { playAudio, getMicrophoneStream } from "@mastra/node-audio";

const agent = new Agent({
  id: "realtime-agent",
  name: "Realtime Voice Agent",
  model: "openai/gpt-5.1",
  instructions: "You speak naturally.",
  voice: new OpenAIRealtimeVoice(),
});

async function main() {
  await agent.voice.connect();

  // play agent audio as it arrives
  agent.voice.on("speaker", ({ audio }) => playAudio(audio));

  // show transcriptions
  agent.voice.on("writing", ({ text, role }) =>
    console.log(`${role}: ${text}`)
  );

  // start conversation
  await agent.voice.speak("Hi! What can I do for you?");

  // stream microphone continuously
  const mic = getMicrophoneStream();
  await agent.voice.send(mic);
}

main();
```

**This gives you real-time talking back and forth.**

